{"id": "143", "post": "<div class=\"post-143 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-editorial tag-bbpress tag-forums\" id=\"post-143\"><h2 class=\"storytitle\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/added-forums-to-talk-about-low-end-stuff/\" rel=\"bookmark\">Added Forums to talk about Low End Stuff</a></h2><div class=\"meta\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" data-src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" alt=\"Tags: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/bbpress/\" rel=\"tag\">bbpress</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/forums/\" rel=\"tag\">forums</a> <img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" alt=\"Date/Time: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> December 15, 2008 @ 10:42 am, by LowEndAdmin</div><div class=\"storycontent tablelook\"><p>I am a bit surprised that there are actually 40-50 visitors to this small website, and many have emailed me the low end stuff that they have found. I think a good way to build the community (yes, due to financial crisis and imminent recession, there\u2019s actually a community for running low-end servers) would be setting up a forum where budget-conscious admins can talk about low end stuff.</p><p>So here we have it. <a href=\"/forums/\">Low End Box Forums</a>.</p><p>Currently running barebone <a href=\"http://bbpress.org/\">bbPress</a>, which I haven\u2019t yet bothered to set up a theme for it. Dump stuff there, and let\u2019s get the talk going.</p><p class=\"dpsp-share-text\"></p><div id=\"dpsp-content-bottom\" class=\"dpsp-content-wrapper dpsp-shape-rounded dpsp-column-auto dpsp-has-spacing dpsp-no-labels dpsp-show-on-mobile dpsp-button-style-1 dpsp-has-icon-background dpsp-has-button-background dpsp-show-total-share-count dpsp-show-total-share-count-after\"><ul class=\"dpsp-networks-btns-wrapper dpsp-netwo